    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a good start. I also want to make sure I'm addressing the counter-argument that \"harmful\" speech (like hate speech or incitement) isn't protected. How would a philosopher using a libertarian framework respond to the idea that the government has a legitimate duty to prevent social harm by regulating that kind of content?",
